<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="292" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1312,1478]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName box="[263,487,1312,1333]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Ficinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="swartruggensis">
<emphasis box="[263,487,1312,1333]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">Ficinia swartruggensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1771: 178) Nees (1833: 91)" authorityName="Nees" authorityPageNumber="91" authorityYear="1833" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityPageNumber="178" baseAuthorityYear="1771" box="[841,1333,1312,1334]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Ficinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bulbosa">
<emphasis box="[841,942,1312,1333]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="292">F. bulbosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C. von" box="[957,1160,1312,1334]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" refId="ref3892" refString="Linnaeus, C. von. (1771) Mantissa Plantarum Altera. Generumeditionis VI &amp; specie rumeditionis II. Holmiae [Stockholm]." type="book" year="1771">Linnaeus, 1771: 178</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Nees von Esenbeck" box="[1175,1333,1312,1334]" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" pagination="75 - 94" refId="ref4081" refString="Nees von Esenbeck (1833) Analecta ad FloramCapensem. Linnaea 8: 75 - 94. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 109830]" type="journal article" year="1833">Nees (1833: 91)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having a tufted habit and spicate inflorescence, but differs in lacks the bulbous culm bases and a spike shortly contracted (vs. lax) with rachis of spikelet heads &lt;
<quantity box="[376,431,1384,1405]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long (vs.&gt; 
<quantity box="[547,602,1384,1406]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="292" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
long).
</paragraph>
